# Implementation Plan - Phase 2: Interactive MCP Flow

# Goal Description
Enable the "Text-to-Graph" flow. User enters a prompt, Maestro analyzes it, calls the Researcher Agent, and updates the Graph on the Canvas.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> **MCP Transport**: We will implement the `stdio` transport for the Python Researcher agent.
> **Gemini Prompts**: We will need to tune the "Meta-Graph" prompt to output structured JSON that Maestro can parse into Graph Nodes.

## Proposed Changes

### Frontend (Canvas)
#### [MODIFY] [frontend/src/App.tsx]
- Add [handleSearch](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstepver2/frontend/src/App.tsx#30-38) function.
- Call `api.sendPrompt(query)`.
- Poll `api.getGraph()` (or similar) to update the canvas.

#### [MODIFY] [frontend/src/services/api.ts]
- Add [getGraph()](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstepver2/frontend/src/services/api.ts#27-36) to fetch current nodes/edges.

### Backend (Maestro)
#### [MODIFY] [backend/main.py]
- POST `/prompt`: Accepts user query, triggers Orchestrator.
- GET `/graph`: Returns current graph state (Nodes/Edges).

#### [MODIFY] [backend/maestro/orchestrator.py]
- Implement [process_request(query)](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstepver2/backend/maestro/orchestrator.py#23-60):
    1.  Ask Gemini: "What tools should I use for '{query}'?"
    2.  Parse Gemini response (Expected: List of Tool Calls).
    3.  **Execute Tool Call**:
        - Spawn/Connect to [agents/researcher/server.py](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstepver2/backend/agents/researcher/server.py) via `stdio` (using `mcp` Client).
        - Send `CallToolRequest`.
        - Receive `CallToolResult`.
    4.  Update Graph (Neo4j + In-Memory).

#### [MODIFY] [backend/agents/researcher/server.py]
- Ensure it accepts standard input/output for MCP protocol.

